Podcast Description An airline captain thought he was giving his children a harmless thrill by letting them "fly" his packed airplane - the young cockpit visitors weren't really in control... the autopilot was doing the real flying. Until it wasn't.&nbsp;
Do safety features actually lull us into a false sense of security - tempting us to take greater risks than we otherwise would?
